panels.name: Radius Server Representation
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=$$Aruba (authmgr) radius
| parse "<*>*:*:* * * *[*]: <*> <*> <* *> *" as pri,throw1,throw2,throw3,throw4,device,module,mod_sys_num,msg_id,log_level,device_co, device_ip, rest_of_msg
| fields - throw1, throw2, throw3, throw4
| parse field=rest_of_msg "RADIUS reject for station * * from server *." as station_name, ap, server | count server | top 10 server by _count

panels.name: Block ACK DoS Attack AP Victims
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=$$Aruba (authmgr or "|ids|") attack "Block ACK"
| parse "<*>*:*:* * * *[*]: <*> <*> <* *> *" as pri,throw1,throw2,throw3,throw4,device,module,mod_sys_num,msg_id,log_level,device_co, device_ip, rest_of_msg
| fields - throw1, throw2, throw3, throw4 
| where module = "wms"
| parse field=rest_of_msg "|ids| AP(*): Block ACK DoS Attack: An AP detected a data frame which indicates a possible Block ACK DoS Attack.  The frame from * (BSSID * on CHANNEL * with SNR *) is outside the current sequence number window, and thus may be dropped. Additional Info: Victim:* TID:* Retry:* Dir:* StartSq:* FrameSq:* EndSq:* BSSID:* . Associated WVE ID(s): WVE-*." as ap, frame_aps, bssid, channel, snr, victim, tid, retry, dir, start_sq, frame_sq, end_sq, throw5, wve_id
| fields - throw5 | count victim | top 100 victim by _count

panels.name: Power Save DoS Attack Channels Trend this Period
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=$$Aruba (authmgr or "|ids|") attack
| parse "<*>*:*:* * * *[*]: <*> <*> <* *> *" as pri,throw1,throw2,throw3,throw4,device,module,mod_sys_num,msg_id,log_level,device_co, device_ip, rest_of_msg
| fields - throw1, throw2, throw3, throw4 
| where module = "wms"
| parse field=rest_of_msg "|ids| AP(*): Power Save DoS Attack: An AP detected a Power Save DoS attack on client * and access point (BSSID * and SSID * on CHANNEL *). SNR of client is *. Additional Info: Pwr-Mgmt-On-Pkts:*; Pwr-Mgmt-Off-Pkts:*." as ap, client, bssid, ssid, channel, snr, pwr_mgmt_on_pkts, pwr_mgmt_off_pkts | timeslice 10 buckets | count _timeslice, channel | transpose row _timeslice column channel

panels.name: Average SNR of Block ACK DoS Attacks this Period
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=$$Aruba (authmgr or "|ids|") attack "Block ACK"
| parse "<*>*:*:* * * *[*]: <*> <*> <* *> *" as pri,throw1,throw2,throw3,throw4,device,module,mod_sys_num,msg_id,log_level,device_co, device_ip, rest_of_msg
| fields - throw1, throw2, throw3, throw4 
| where module = "wms"
| parse field=rest_of_msg "|ids| AP(*): Block ACK DoS Attack: An AP detected a data frame which indicates a possible Block ACK DoS Attack.  The frame from * (BSSID * on CHANNEL * with SNR *) is outside the current sequence number window, and thus may be dropped. Additional Info: Victim:* TID:* Retry:* Dir:* StartSq:* FrameSq:* EndSq:* BSSID:* . Associated WVE ID(s): WVE-*." as ap, frame_aps, bssid, channel, snr, victim, tid, retry, dir, start_sq, frame_sq, end_sq, throw5, wve_id
| fields - throw5
| timeslice 1h
| avg(snr) as avg_snr by _timeslice
| outlier avg_snr

panels.name: Role and Policy Trend this Period
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=$$Aruba (authmgr) srcip
